What a shame, this is basically just a money grab.  They should have stayed true to ALL of Arethas wishes and used her script.

snippet.textDisplay: I hope this is good and not rushed or tacky. Aretha's voice, music and legacy is absolutely phenomenal. If you listen to her early stuff from 1960-1964 long before Respect was released, she sang and performed some beautiful soulful tracks such as "Losing You" and "I can't wait until I see my baby's face". She also sang lots of Jazz in the early days such as "Tiny Sparrow" and "Won't be Long". I am praying this is nothing like Dreamgirls, but more detailed and soulful.
